# File Naming: Use kebab-case

All files in the project must use **kebab-case** naming convention.

## Rules:

- Use lowercase letters and hyphens only
- Separate words with hyphens (`-`)
- Examples:
  - ✅ `loading-spinner.tsx`
  - ✅ `error-display.tsx`
  - ✅ `service-selection.tsx`
  - ❌ `LoadingSpinner.tsx` (PascalCase)
  - ❌ `loadingSpinner.tsx` (camelCase)
  - ❌ `loading_spinner.tsx` (snake_case)

## Applies to:

- All TypeScript/JavaScript files (`.ts`, `.tsx`, `.js`, `.jsx`)
- All component files
- All utility files
- All configuration files

## Exception:

- Single-word files can remain as-is (e.g., `index.tsx`, `header.tsx`)
